com.github.fedorchuck.jsqlb

Interface DataTypes

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    PGDataTypes
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BIGINT, BIGSERIAL, BIT, BIT_VARYING, BOOLEAN, BOX, BYTEA, CHAR, CHARACTER, CHARACTER_VARYING, CIDR, CIRCLE, DATE, FLOAT8, INET, INT, JSON, JSONB, LINE, LSEG, MACADDR, MONEY, PATH, PG_LSN, POINT, POLYGON, REAL, SERIAL, SMALLINT, SMALLSERIAL, TEXT, TIME, TIMESTAMP, TIMESTAMPTZ, TIMETZ, TSQUERY, TSVECTOR, TXID_SNAPSHOT, UUID, VARBIT, VARCHAR, XML

    public interface DataTypes
    DataTypes of a class is enabled by the class implementing the com.github.fedorchuck.DataTypes interface. The DataTypes interface has no methods or fields and serves only to identify the semantics of contain DataTypes of database. While creating table, for each column, you specify a data type, i.e., what kind of data you want to store in the table fields.

    Since:
    0.1.0
